messages.content: are there any interesting things happening in san francisco today?

For film enthusiasts, the **SF Frozen Film Festival** is running from today until July 20 at the Roxie Theater and other locations, showcasing new independent avant-garde pop culture films [bernalconnect](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [funcheap](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [pacificedgesf](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2). Other music events include performances by **Alison Krauss and Union Station, Jerry Douglas & Willie Watson**, **Rakim**, **Frankie & The Witch Fingers** at The Chapel, **Sematary** at The Independent, **Howard Wiley** at the Great American Music Hall, and **The Fin.(Japan)** [san-francisco](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [san-francisco-theater](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [songkick](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9]. Note that Robert Earl Keen is performing at the Golden State Theatre in Monterey [san-francisco-theater](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [songkick](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-9].

There are also several free events, including free **Tai Chi** sessions at Union Square Plaza, free admission to the **Japanese Tea Garden** in Golden Gate Park from 9:00 AM to 10:00 AM, a free family storytime at Salesforce Park at 10:00 AM, and free admission to the **Yerba Buena Center for the Arts (YBCA)** from 11:00 AM to 5:00 PM [funcheap](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). The **"People in Plazas" Market Street Free Summer Music Festival** is ongoing, offering 130 free summer concerts from July 8 to September 24 [funcheap](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [funcheap](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6). As part of the **Golden Gate Bandshell Concerts**, there will be a Singer/Songwriter Wednesday event from 4:30 PM to 7:30 PM [sfrecpark](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7).

If you're interested in exploring the city, **San Francisco City Guides** is offering several walking tours, including Japanese Tea Garden, Coit Tower Murals, Haight-Ashbury, Gold Rush City, and Mission Bay: Hidden Waters [sfcityguides](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-10]. You could also take a **Golden Gate Bridge and Lombard GoCar Tour** [myguidesanfrancisco](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-11].

Other events include the **Walnut Creek's Locust Street Festival** [funcheap](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [funcheap](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5) and the **Visionary Founder Vibe Coding Vibeathon** at 988 Columbus Ave [sftravel](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8).

Finally, be aware that the **SFMTA** has issued a transit and traffic advisory for the week, including information about event-related traffic impacts [sfmta](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-13).
